FBIS4-15924 "drsov071_b_94005" FBIS-SOV-94-071 Daily Report 12 Apr 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Political Issues `Experts' List Most Influential Parliamentarians `Experts' List Most Influential Parliamentarians LD1304002394 Moscow INTERFAX in English 2101 GMT 12 Apr 94 LD1304002394 Moscow INTERFAX English BFN [Text] The speaker of the State Duma Ivan Rybkin, leader of the faction Russia's Choice, Egor Gaydar and head of the Communist party faction Gennadiy Zyuganov in March exerted the greatest influence on decision-making in parliament. Such are the results of an opinion poll conducted by the Independent Center of Russian Political Culture Studies. Experts of the center, among them parliamentary journalists and political experts, determined the rating of Duma deputies' political influence in March on a 10-point scale. The top twenty after Rybkin (8.2), Gaydar (6.3) and Zyuganov (6.3) include Vladimir Zhirinovskiy (5.4), Sergey Shakhray (5.3), Sergey Glazyev (4.9), Mikhail Lapshin (4.8), Konstantin Zatulin (4.6), Vladimir Lukin (4.5). Anatoliy Lukyanov (4.4), Viktor Ilyukhin (4.3), Vladimir Isakov (4.2), Aleksandr Vengerovskiy (4.1), Sergey Baburin (4.0), Vassiliy Lipitskiy (3.8), Mikhail Zadornov (3.7), Girgoriy Yavlinskiy (3.6), Aleksandr Pochinok (3.6), Aleksandr Nazarchuk (3.5) and Gennadiy Burbulis (3.5). The commentary on results of the poll will be published in the Megapolis-Continent newspaper on Thursday.
